SIMPLE: steely
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Steely
<hw>Steel"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made
of steel; consisting of steel.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>steely</xex> point
of Clifford's lance.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Around his shop the <qex>steely</qex> sparkles flew.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling steel; hard; firm; having the color of
steel.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His hair was <xex>steely</xex> gray.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>The Century.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She would unarm her noble heart of that <qex>steely</qex>
resistance against the sweet blows of love.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Steely iron</b></col>, <cd>a compound of iron containing
less than one half of one per cent of carbon.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steelyard</ent>⟦br⟧
